</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-32_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-33_ pf-text-1"><strong>Cardiopulmonary Resuscitation (CPR)</strong> - CPR is a lifesaving technique that involves chest compressions and rescue breaths to maintain blood flow and oxygenation to the body's vital organs during cardiac arrest.





</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-35_ pf-text-1"><strong>Cardiac arrest </strong>- occurs when the heart suddenly stops beating, causing blood flow to the brain and other vital organs to cease.




</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-iqseJM ducrfW pf-37_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-38_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bTfYFJ fFWOZc pf-39_ pf-heading-1-h3">Relevant legislation, regulations, and best practice</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-41_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-42_ pf-text-1"><strong>Health and Safety (First Aid) Regulations 1981 </strong>- These regulations require employers to provide adequate first aid training for their employees, including CPR training.






</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-44_ pf-text-1"><strong>Resuscitation Council UK guidelines</strong> - These guidelines provide evidence-based recommendations for CPR techniques, including the ratio of chest compressions to rescue breaths and automated external defibrillators (AEDs).





